data.name: Column
desc: describes the common properties of a database column.

properties.name: DefaultValue
desc: keeps a default value for a column, is provided as string.

properties.name: Description
desc: keeps a description of the object.

properties.name: IsAutoIncrement
desc: indicates whether the column is automatically numbered, thus read-only.

properties.name: IsCurrency
desc: indicates whether the column is a cash value.

properties.name: IsNullable
desc: indicates the nullability of values in the designated column.

properties.name: IsRowVersion
desc: indicates that the column contains some kind of time or date stamp used to track updates.

properties.name: Name
desc: is the name of the column.

properties.name: Precision
desc: gets a column's number of decimal digits.

properties.name: Scale
desc: gets a column's number of digits to right of the decimal point.

properties.name: Type
desc: is the com.sun.star.sdbc.DataType of the column.

properties.name: TypeName
desc: is the type name used by the database.
If the column type is a user-defined type, then a fully-qualified type name is returned.  Note:  May be empty.
